66	URBANNAV: DEVELOPMENT OF URBAN COMMUTING SYSTEM WITH INTELLIGENCE ROUTE MAPPING AND DYNAMIC FARE ESTIMATION	Iloilo City, as a rapidly growing urban center, experiences a high volume of daily commuters and tourists, relying heavily on Public Utility Jeepneys (PUJs) for transportation. However, commuters often face difficulties identifying the most efficient PUJ routes and estimating fares, leading to longer travel times and higher costs, particularly for unfamiliar tourists. To address these issues, this study developed UrbanNav: Development of Urban Commuting System with Intelligent Route Mapping and Dynamic Fare Estimation, a mobile application that integrates GPS and Dijkstra’s algorithm to compute the shortest PUJ routes and provide real-time navigation, fare estimation based on LTFRB standards, and traffic-aware alternatives using Google Maps. Developed using the Agile Software Development Model, UrbanNav followed an iterative process of planning, development, testing, and feedback integration. The system was evaluated based on ISO 25010 software quality standards. Overall, UrbanNav earned an average rating of 4.5 (Excellent), signifying its effectiveness and potential impact on Iloilo City’s transportation sector. In conclusion, UrbanNav is a functional, secure, and highly usable mobile solution for urban commuters. It effectively resolves long-standing navigation and fare estimation challenges and shows strong promise for future enhancements in scalability, adaptability, and system maintenance.	BSIT
